    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659a.119/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-23T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6673. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 124. Your 8540, February 6. Our 88, February 11,<note n="1" xml:id="d428fn1"
                        >Not printed.</note> notified you of our refusal license imports of wool.
                    Hereafter will hold all export and import licenses of Icelandic products pending
                    your negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
